Sequence Information.Peptide Name: RTD-5 (rhesus macaque theta-defensin-5; natural AMPs; monkey, primates, mammals, animals; 3S=S, Cys-rich; UCBB1ab; XXC; Other AMPs? RTD-6)

Literature Information.Literature: Active against S. aureus 502a, E. coli ML 35, and C. albicans 16820. RTD-1 and RTD-5 are 3-fold more active than RTD-4. RTD-6 has not be collected due to the lack of activity data. Chemical synthesis and purification of RTD-6 turned out to be more difficult than other RTD defensins.
Literature Information.Author: Tongaonkar P, Tran P, Roberts K, Schaal J, Osapay G, Tran D, Ouellette AJ, Selsted ME.2011
Literature Information.Title: Rhesus macaque {theta}-defensin isoforms: expression, antimicrobial activities, and demonstration of a prominent role in neutrophil granule microbicidal activities
